**Overall meaning:**

"Even crores of thousands of minor sins disappear from the chanting of the mantra of Rama."

**Interpretation:**

This verse emphasizes the immense power of chanting the name of Rama (a form of Vishnu, a major deity in Hinduism). It suggests that even minor sins, which are numerous and potentially very difficult to overcome, can be eradicated through the constant repetition of this sacred sound. This verse highlights the power of devotion and the transformative nature of chanting in the Hindu tradition. 
